The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Advani grabs title

Pune: National champion Pankaj Advani displayed his superb form as he thrashed Thai challenger C. Praput 5-0 to win the fourth Asian billiards championship here on Saturday. 

Beginning confidently, advani went on to win all the five frames without much challenge despite his rival being a former world champion and one who has caused major upsets in the ongoing championship. 

Advani set up the game from the first frame itself. He had an unfinished break of 90 in the first in which Praput was able to manage 64 points. The second frame saw Advani consolidate his lead as he won the game with an unfinished break of 63. By the time the third frame ended, the result was a forgone conclusion. 

Advani won the third and fourth frames with unfinished breaks of 81 and 94, respectively. (PTI) 




